<center>
<H2>
  Contact Information
</H2>
<H3>
Rare Book, Manuscript,<br>and Special Collections Library<br>Duke University
</H3>
</center>
  <HR>

<p>Following is information about who to contact at the library depending on what information
you need.</p>

<p><a href="/">General information about the library</a> and <a href="/#guides">various
collection guides and finding aids</a> are available to help you find what you are looking
for, and we encourage everyone to consult these resources before contacting us with
questions.</p>

<p>Unfortunately we are unable to answer very general questions on all historical topics. If
your question is very broad or does not relate directly to materials in the Duke University
Rare Book, Manuscript, and Special Collections Library, you will probably have better success
by contacting your local school or public library reference librarian first.</p>

<br>

<h3>E-mail / telephone</h3>

<blockquote><i>

<p>If you are getting in touch via e-mail, please be sure to include your return e-mail
address in the <b>body</b> of the message, since it sometimes gets stripped from the header in
transit.  Also, if you expect a response, make sure to include a phone or fax number or postal
address where we can reach you, since sometimes it is difficult or impossible to respond via
e-mail. Thank you! <p>

</i></blockquote>

<br>

<p><b>General information</b>: For reference questions, questions about finding materials in
the library's collections and how you can use them, requesting permission to reproduce, or
other information.</p>
<ul>
<li>E-mail: <A href="mailto:special-collections@duke.edu">special-collections@duke.edu</A>
<li>Phone: 919-660-5822
<li>Fax: 919-660-5934
</ul> <br>


<p><a href="/hartman/"><b>Hartman Center for Sales, Advertising, and Marketing
History</b></a>: For questions about the library's advertising history collections.</p>
<ul>
<li>E-mail: <a href="mailto:hartman-center@duke.edu">hartman-center@duke.edu</a>
<li>Phone: 919-660-5827
</ul>
<br>

<p><a href="/women/"><b>Center for Women's History and Culture</b></a>: For questions about the library's
women's studies materials. </p>

<ul>
<li>E-mail: <a href="mailto:cwhc@duke.edu">cwhc@duke.edu</a>
<li>Phone: 919-660-5967
</ul>
<br>


<p><a href="/franklin/"><b>John Hope Franklin Collection of African and African-American
Documentation</b></a>: For questions about the library's African and African-American studies
materials.</p>

<ul>
<li>E-mail: <a href="mailto:franklin-center@duke.edu">franklin-collection@duke.edu</a>
<li>Phone: 919-660-5922
</ul>
<br>

<p><b>Administrative offices</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Phone: 919-660-5820
<li>Fax: 919-660-5934
</ul>


<br>

<p>For information on individual staff members' phone numbers and e-mail addresses, see our <A
HREF="/specoll/staff.html">Library Staff</A> page.</P>

